76
00:06:51,330 --> 00:06:52,170
That's me.

77
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:53,370
I was telling you

78
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,250
to come down for breakfast.

79
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,090
Morning, morning.

80
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,790
Can I borrow your test paper?

81
00:06:58,790 --> 00:07:00,450
I slept last night
and didn't finish mine.

82
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:05,700
Okay.

83
00:07:06,290 --> 00:07:08,290
I'll go get it. You go down first.

84
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,250
Thanks.

85
00:07:17,660 --> 00:07:19,700
I hope you can spend more time with them

86
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,700
and take good care of them.

87
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:23,080
Otherwise, what's the point of me
traveling and being busy all the time?

88
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:23,940
But...

89
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:26,450
You told me about
what happened to Tian before.

90
00:07:26,450 --> 00:07:28,250
You don't want it to happen again, right?

91
00:07:29,410 --> 00:07:31,040
Alright, just listen to me.

92
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:32,460
But...

93
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:35,160
Hey, Wang.

94
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,450
Come and have breakfast.

95
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:38,200
Come on, hurry.

96
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:40,200
I'm going on a business trip today.

97
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,660
I have to go to the airport later.

98
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,500
Oh. Hello?

99
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,540
Yes?

100
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,040
Yeah.

101
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,950
Wang, have some veggies.

102
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:53,910
Where's Tian?

103
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:55,200
Oh, he is...

104
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:59,370
Why are you just standing there?

105
00:07:59,370 --> 00:08:00,290
Come eat.

106
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,620
Come on, sit here.

107
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,040
Come on.

108
00:08:27,330 --> 00:08:28,250
I'm full.

109
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:30,040
Are you full?

110
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:39,080
I'm full too.

111
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:41,830
But you only had a sip of milk.

112
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:43,330
Okay. Yeah.

113
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,250
Where are the boys?

114
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:53,450
Wang had all the porridge I made today.

115
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,660
Really?

116
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:55,830
He must've been hungry.

117
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,160
I'm hungry too.

118
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,160
Sheng Wang.

119
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:24,910
I'm used to your mom's breakfast.

120
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,830
I don't need your hawthorn slices.
Thank you.

121
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:03,770
(Student Dormitory Application Form)

122
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:28,270
(I agree to the
above accommodation rules.)

123
00:10:36,330 --> 00:10:37,700
Yesterday, you waited for me.

124
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:38,910
Today, it's my turn to wait for you.

125
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,540
Hurry down for breakfast.

126
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,910
Looks like your mom decided to stay.

127
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:49,200
What? What about my mom?

128
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,540
Nothing.

129
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:51,540
Let's go.

130
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:56,870
Let's go.

131
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:06,020
(Morning self-study, please keep quiet.)

132
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:15,020
(Morning self-study, please keep quiet.)

133
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,250
Jing said no copying.

134
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,410
You're still doing it.

135
00:11:26,870 --> 00:11:28,660
Wow, you're fast.

136
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,950
No wonder you got away
from those punks last time.

137
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:32,750
As long as you know that.

138
00:11:59,250 --> 00:12:00,090
Thanks.

139
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:14,200
Let's go to Old Man Ding's for lunch.

140
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,000
Okay.

141
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:35,750
Back. Back.

142
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:37,750
Over here, over here.

143
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,330
Okay.

144
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:47,830
Mr. Sheng?

145
00:12:48,290 --> 00:12:49,130
Which room should it go to?

146
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:50,700
This one.

147
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:51,580
Please sign here.

148
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:52,580
Okay. Thanks.

149
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:59,910
Why did you buy me a new fridge?

150
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,330
Your old one couldn't keep things cold.

151
00:13:02,330 --> 00:13:05,290
You can put your things that were
about to go bad into this one.

152
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:07,080
But, you bought a new fridge...

153
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:09,000
Alright, consider it my food bill

154
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,580
and payment to you, the chef.

155
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:11,870
But you have to let me

156
00:13:11,870 --> 00:13:13,250
have lunch here every day.

157
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,160
No, no.

158
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,160
You should've told me
before replacing my fridge.

159
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,790
Why did you do this

160
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:20,080
on your own?

161
00:13:20,450 --> 00:13:22,290
If you disagree,

162
00:13:22,290 --> 00:13:24,250
I won't come here for lunch anymore.

163
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:27,410
Fine, don't come since you've got pride.

164
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,700
Come on.

165
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:31,950
Grandpa Ding, please.

166
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:33,620
Can you bear to see me

167
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:34,830
fighting for food in the cafeteria?

168
00:13:34,830 --> 00:13:36,160
And I can't compete with others.

169
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:38,580
Besides, moving the new fridge out

170
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:39,620
will cost money.

171
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:41,200
Also, I already had the old fridge

172
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,790
hauled off, so it's gone for good.

173
00:13:44,290 --> 00:13:45,130
But really,

174
00:13:45,140 --> 00:13:48,080
couldn't you have talked to me first?

175
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:49,790
I can't stand you.

176
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:51,870
So, am I thoughtful or what?

177
00:13:52,410 --> 00:13:55,370
Come on. I knew you needed it,

178
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:56,790
so I bought... Wait, no.

179
00:13:56,790 --> 00:13:58,540
I placed a fridge here.

180
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:01,950
Is he your friend?

181
00:14:01,950 --> 00:14:03,450
Aren't you going to do anything?

182
00:14:03,950 --> 00:14:05,500
Even my dad can't do anything about me.

183
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,040
Good for you.

184
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:09,830
Alright.

185
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:12,000
I told my dad about this

186
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,950
and he approved it.

187
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:14,500
Or, where would I get the money?

188
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,410
Alright, I need to use the bathroom now.

189
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:23,700
I think your friend is better than you.

190
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:27,330
I treat him well,
but he treats me better.

191
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:30,040
He is polite, you know.

192
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,910
But who do you need to be polite to?

193
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:35,620
Only to strangers, right?

194
00:14:35,620 --> 00:14:37,080
If he sees me as one of his own,

195
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,790
he wouldn't be so polite.

196
00:14:40,660 --> 00:14:43,250
So, be direct. He fears

197
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:45,330
owing others and becoming distant.

198
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:50,250
It's best not to get
too involved with others.

199
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:51,660
No connections, no ties.

200
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,250
But,

201
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,540
I think it's pretty wise.

202
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:59,910
People should keep
their distance, right?

203
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:01,080
Otherwise, if something bad happens,

204
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:03,330
it wouldn't be good
to get dragged into it.

205
00:15:04,580 --> 00:15:06,870
You know, a hedge between
keeps friendship green.

206
00:15:10,290 --> 00:15:11,580
I even persuaded you

207
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:13,700
to get closer to him.

208
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,870
But I didn't expect you
to be the same type.

209
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:24,410
- Come on. Eat.
- Yes, sir.

210
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:25,790
Did you wash your hands?

211
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:27,120
Just finished.

212
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,450
- Alright, eat up.
- Oh, what's this?

213
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:32,160
You still have classes after lunch, right?

214
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,410
I'll leave you to it.

215
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,910
Wow, that's spicy.

216
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,330
Why are you giving me this?

217
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,580
Weren't you just burning up?

218
00:16:10,450 --> 00:16:11,290
Thanks.

219
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:12,750
I should buy you one too.

220
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:15,910
Which one should I get?

221
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,040
Do you like this one?

222
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,790
It's a sparkling, alkaline drink

223
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,120
with some juice in it.

224
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:26,040
So, be direct. He fears

225
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,120
owing others and becoming distant.

226
00:16:28,870 --> 00:16:31,580
It's best not to get
too involved with others.

227
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:32,870
No connections, no ties.

228
00:16:35,830 --> 00:16:37,000
I don't want it.

229
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:40,000
Mr. Zhao, money for the water.

230
00:16:44,950 --> 00:16:46,330
Mr. Zhao, I bought one too.

231
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:50,580
Take it.

232
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:52,950
Hey, take it!

233
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,790
You just hate owing people,

234
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:58,700
don't you?

235
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:00,950
Because I need to pay it back.

236
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,740
Have anyone asked you to pay it back?

237
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,160
No.

238
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:08,040
But,

239
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,660
if I owe something,
it stays on my mind.

240
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:11,290
It piles up and weighs on me.

241
00:17:11,290 --> 00:17:12,500
Then I'll be unhappy.

242
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:17,290
So you put it down,

243
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:19,040
right?

244
00:17:20,870 --> 00:17:21,950
What do you mean?

245
00:17:21,950 --> 00:17:23,160
Just take it.

246
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,410
I don't want it.

247
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:27,290
Hey, you always do this.

248
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:28,790
Don't walk so fast.
You're being childish.

249
00:17:28,790 --> 00:17:30,580
Don't you want to keep your distance from me?

250
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,120
Then don't follow me.

251
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:39,660
Great to see everyone

252
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:41,910
so energetic for
the first afternoon class.

253
00:18:41,910 --> 00:18:44,500
Then no one should be dozing off.

254
00:18:44,870 --> 00:18:46,160
Wake up.

255
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,450
Next time I catch someone nodding off,

256
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,950
I'll make them run three laps
on the playground.

257
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,040
Gao Tianyang.

258
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,330
Gao Tianyang.

259
00:18:57,290 --> 00:18:58,500
Gao Tianyang!

260
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:00,830
So, do you want to run three laps?

261
00:19:02,410 --> 00:19:03,410
What three laps?

262
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:06,160
Alright, everyone,
take out your textbooks.

263
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,750
Oh, right, one more thing.

264
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:11,330
Next week, we'll have
a parent-teacher meeting.

265
00:19:11,330 --> 00:19:12,870
Let your parents know.

266
00:19:12,870 --> 00:19:14,080
All the teachers and I

267
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:15,910
will discuss each of your situations

268
00:19:15,910 --> 00:19:17,450
with your parents.

269
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:19,830
If you have any special circumstances,

270
00:19:19,830 --> 00:19:21,040
tell me after this class.

271
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:23,540
Now, let's go over
last time's exercises.

272
