273
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:31,200
Alright, make sure to memorize

274
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,540
today's key points and formulas.

275
00:19:32,540 --> 00:19:33,500
Class dismissed.

276
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:35,660
Thank you, sir.

277
00:19:52,870 --> 00:19:54,160
Hello, Old Sheng,

278
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:56,200
when will you come back?

279
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,000
Next Thursday or Friday.

280
00:19:58,500 --> 00:19:59,340
No,

281
00:19:59,450 --> 00:20:01,080
probably the week after the next.

282
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,910
Then just say you don't know.

283
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:04,200
I don't know.

284
00:20:06,370 --> 00:20:08,160
Fine, I'm going to class. Talk to you later.

285
00:20:09,180 --> 00:20:13,720
(Contacts)

286
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:14,950
Sir.

287
00:20:14,950 --> 00:20:16,410
I want to ask you a question.

288
00:20:16,410 --> 00:20:17,450
I have a question too.

289
00:20:20,870 --> 00:20:21,830
Oh. Hello?

290
00:20:22,450 --> 00:20:24,750
Mr. Chen? This is Wang.

291
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:27,500
Can you be my dad again?

292
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,040
We'll have another parent-teacher meeting.

293
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:31,000
You called the wrong person.

294
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,120
Jiang Tian?

295
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:39,070
♪Our encounter♪

296
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:41,540
I'll hang up then.

297
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:43,390
Okay.

298
00:20:43,390 --> 00:20:49,140
♪Cannot be avoided, like this heavy rain♪

299
00:20:49,670 --> 00:20:56,320
♪Our youth, like the frozen time♪

300
00:20:56,800 --> 00:21:02,560
♪This moment is eternity.
I run towards you♪

301
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:10,120
♪In the dark valley,
you will catch my heart♪

302
00:21:15,410 --> 00:21:16,250
Hey!

303
00:21:17,830 --> 00:21:18,950
I've been looking for you!

304
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:19,870
Bathroom?

305
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:21,250
I'm not going.

306
00:21:21,620 --> 00:21:22,750
I'll go to the office.

307
00:21:23,660 --> 00:21:24,700
Why?

308
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:27,500
A special circumstance.

309
00:21:27,910 --> 00:21:29,330
A special circumstance?

310
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:31,790
What is a special circumstance?

311
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:33,250
A special circumstance?

312
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:34,620
You know, a special circumstance.

313
00:21:34,870 --> 00:21:37,080
What? Did I get it on me?

314
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:39,040
- I got it on me, right?
- Got what on you?

315
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,910
Keep it down.

316
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,160
What is it? Keep it down.

317
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,160
You! Go to the bathroom! Go, go, go!

318
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,660
- Gao Tianyang...
- I'll cover for you. Go!

319
00:21:46,660 --> 00:21:47,830
Alright, what are you doing?

320
00:21:47,830 --> 00:21:48,670
Just go to the bathroom.

321
00:21:48,670 --> 00:21:50,080
Wait. Lower your voice.

322
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:51,080
Gao Tianyang...

323
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:53,660
After you're done, wait for me
by the bathroom door.

324
00:21:53,660 --> 00:21:55,080
I'll go to the classroom
and grab a jacket.

325
00:21:55,910 --> 00:21:57,500
A jacket? For what?

326
00:21:58,580 --> 00:22:00,950
Come on. That's ketchup.

327
00:22:04,850 --> 00:22:06,930
(Ladies' Room)

328
00:22:06,930 --> 00:22:09,930
(Parent-Teacher Meeting
Contacts and Notes)

329
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:20,660
- Sir.
- Yes. What's wrong?

330
00:22:20,660 --> 00:22:22,200
My dad can't make it to the meeting.

331
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:28,370
The school scheduled it on the weekend

332
00:22:28,370 --> 00:22:30,250
to avoid weekdays.

333
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:32,120
This meeting is quite important.

334
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,790
Could you ask your father
to spare some time,

335
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:35,160
just for 30 minutes?

336
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:37,080
He can't make it.

337
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:38,700
How about 20 minutes?

338
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:39,950
Just enough for a quick chat.

339
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:40,950
He can leave right after.

340
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,370
Not even 20 minutes?

341
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,290
How about this?

342
00:22:53,290 --> 00:22:55,330
Ask him when he'll be free

343
00:22:55,330 --> 00:22:56,620
to come over.

344
00:22:56,620 --> 00:22:57,700
I'll wait for him.

345
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,910
He's been traveling a lot lately.

346
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,500
Sir, I'll catch him
and bring him to you

347
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:03,700
as soon as he's available.

348
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,000
Is that okay?

349
00:23:05,540 --> 00:23:06,450
How about your mom?

350
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:10,040
My mom passed away.

351
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,790
She passed away when I was little.

352
00:23:13,750 --> 00:23:15,950
Then, who attended

353
00:23:15,950 --> 00:23:16,950
your meetings before?

354
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:20,660
- I...
- Excuse me.

355
00:23:21,250 --> 00:23:22,200
Come in.

356
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:24,810
What's the matter?

357
00:23:24,830 --> 00:23:26,870
Sir, my mom can't make it

358
00:23:27,330 --> 00:23:28,290
to the meeting.

359
00:23:28,540 --> 00:23:29,790
- Your mom too?
- Didn't your mom...

360
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:30,830
She's busy.

361
00:23:35,370 --> 00:23:36,330
My parents are divorced.

362
00:23:36,330 --> 00:23:37,580
I live with my mom now.

363
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:40,480
You two planned this, didn't you?

364
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:42,950
Never mind.

365
00:23:42,950 --> 00:23:45,040
The parents of the top student

366
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:46,410
and the most improved one can't come.

367
00:23:46,410 --> 00:23:48,000
What can I say?

368
00:23:50,290 --> 00:23:51,330
How about this?

369
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:53,370
Why don't you two pair up?

370
00:23:53,370 --> 00:23:55,410
Ask your parents when they'll be free.

371
00:23:55,410 --> 00:23:56,540
I can work around

372
00:23:56,540 --> 00:23:57,540
their schedules.

373
00:23:57,830 --> 00:24:00,140
Then the three of us
will have a small meeting.

374
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,000
Okay. That's a deal.

375
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,540
Don't forget to ask your parents.

376
00:24:04,540 --> 00:24:05,790
Since you're both here,

377
00:24:05,790 --> 00:24:07,410
go see Director Xu. Go.

378
00:24:07,410 --> 00:24:08,450
Go on.

379
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:12,330
Didn't your mom agree
not to travel with my dad?

380
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:22,910
Hey, what's your problem?

381
00:24:22,910 --> 00:24:24,330
Want to fight again?

382
00:24:24,870 --> 00:24:25,790
Zhai Tao,

383
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,580
why don't you count how many times

384
00:24:27,910 --> 00:24:29,870
you've been called to
my office this month?

385
00:24:29,870 --> 00:24:31,370
Who's that in the middle?

386
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:34,080
He's Ding Xiu,

387
00:24:34,410 --> 00:24:37,660
the one who tricked you
into fetching the test papers.

388
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,910
Are you the victim or not?

389
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:43,330
Sorry, sir. I'm face-blind.

390
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:49,000
I'll make it brief.

391
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,700
Two punks caused trouble at our shop.

392
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:52,940
Linzi and I caught them.

393
00:24:53,910 --> 00:24:55,370
One confessed

394
00:24:55,370 --> 00:24:57,330
his sworn brother
had been embarrassed at school

395
00:24:57,330 --> 00:24:58,750
so he wanted revenge.

396
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:01,000
Then, he sneaked onto campus

397
00:25:01,410 --> 00:25:03,080
and looked for someone to do it for him.

398
00:25:03,580 --> 00:25:07,290
This one is the brother
who had been embarrassed.

399
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:10,500
And Sheng Wang is
the target of the revenge.

400
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:12,160
Come on.

401
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:15,290
I just wanted to scare him, not beat him up.

402
00:25:16,410 --> 00:25:18,000
But he told me

403
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,290
this test was crucial for Sheng Wang.

404
00:25:20,290 --> 00:25:22,080
If he failed, it would be
a huge blow to him.

405
00:25:22,540 --> 00:25:24,040
It was all his idea.

406
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,830
Ask my sworn brother
if you don't believe me.

407
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:27,540
It was really you, Qi?

408
00:25:30,450 --> 00:25:31,700
It wasn't me.

409
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:34,450
I barely spoke to them.

410
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:35,830
They two did wrong

411
00:25:35,830 --> 00:25:37,700
and blamed me!

412
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:40,120
What are you talking about?

413
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:41,870
You pretend not to know me
after joining Class A?

414
00:25:41,870 --> 00:25:43,000
Are you kidding me?

415
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,790
Why would I accuse you for no reason?

416
00:25:44,790 --> 00:25:46,870
How should I know why you did it?

417
00:25:46,870 --> 00:25:49,160
What's it got to do with me
joining Class A?

418
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:52,500
You're not a good person,
so I don't want to hang out with you.

419
00:25:52,950 --> 00:25:54,330
You better explain yourself!

420
00:25:54,330 --> 00:25:55,500
You told me

421
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:56,700
this exam was crucial for him

422
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:58,290
and you wanted me
to stop him from taking it.

423
00:25:58,290 --> 00:26:00,200
I never said that.

424
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,000
Don't make things up. Show some proof!

425
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:02,840
You didn't...

426
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:04,950
Enough!

427
00:26:04,950 --> 00:26:07,120
I didn't call you here
to make a dramatic scene.

428
00:26:12,330 --> 00:26:13,250
Qi Jiahao.

429
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:17,450
I know you're competitive
and care about grades.

430
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,250
But now,

431
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:22,250
I'm very disappointed in you.

432
00:26:23,330 --> 00:26:24,330
Jing...

433
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,450
I...

434
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:31,500
You all know exactly

435
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:33,870
what happened.

436
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:36,250
Regardless of your intentions,

437
00:26:36,250 --> 00:26:39,870
you made Sheng Wang
miss the listening test.

438
00:26:40,290 --> 00:26:44,040
You may think one test
isn't a big deal for him.

439
00:26:44,290 --> 00:26:46,580
There's always another chance
if he fails this time.

440
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:49,660
But what if you hadn't
been caught this time?

441
00:26:49,660 --> 00:26:51,410
What if this student

442
00:26:51,410 --> 00:26:53,080
loses the model student title

443
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:55,040
and it changes his life?

444
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,700
Have you considered that?

445
00:26:57,660 --> 00:27:00,870
The university entrance exam
isn't the end of the road,

446
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:03,200
but it can impact someone's future.

447
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:06,120
You worked hard to be a model student,

448
00:27:06,580 --> 00:27:09,410
but you've trampled
on someone else's efforts.

449
00:27:10,500 --> 00:27:12,500
Do you think you deserve the title?

450
00:27:14,370 --> 00:27:16,250
I'll have your class advisor reassess.

451
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:18,620
Your title is revoked.

452
00:27:18,950 --> 00:27:19,790
And

453
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:21,290
the three of you

454
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:23,500
will each receive a major demerit.

455
00:27:25,500 --> 00:27:27,870
As for the model student title,

456
00:27:27,870 --> 00:27:29,700
since you showed the most improvement

457
00:27:29,700 --> 00:27:32,160
over two tests,

458
00:27:32,410 --> 00:27:34,370
I'll keep it for you.

459
00:27:34,660 --> 00:27:35,580
I don't want it.

460
00:27:35,910 --> 00:27:36,750
What?

461
00:27:37,540 --> 00:27:38,660
I said I don't want it.

462
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:41,620
I didn't advance 50 places,

463
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:44,200
so I don't want the title.

464
00:27:45,290 --> 00:27:46,330
Fine.

465
00:27:46,830 --> 00:27:48,120
Whatever makes you happy.

466
00:27:49,620 --> 00:27:50,500
Jiang Tian.

467
00:27:50,790 --> 00:27:52,790
Now you're the only one

468
00:27:52,790 --> 00:27:54,540
of the four model students
left in your class.

469
00:27:54,540 --> 00:27:55,500
No.

470
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:58,620
Now, we have none.

471
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:00,700
What do you mean?

472
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:01,830
Make it clear.

473
00:28:01,830 --> 00:28:03,080
We both fought,

474
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:05,200
so we should be punished equally.

475
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:08,040
It's unfair if I keep the title

476
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:08,880
and he doesn't.

477
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:09,750
Well...

478
00:28:09,750 --> 00:28:11,410
Did I take it from him?

479
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,370
Director Xu.

480
00:28:14,370 --> 00:28:16,000
Honestly,

481
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,910
it really is because of
the conditions you set.

482
00:28:20,450 --> 00:28:21,870
Alright. Alright.

483
00:28:21,870 --> 00:28:23,370
Neither of you want it.

484
00:28:23,700 --> 00:28:25,580
Let's see how you feel about this later.

485
00:28:27,890 --> 00:28:31,350
(Student Affairs)

486
00:28:32,870 --> 00:28:35,160
Why did you give up
the model student title?

487
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:36,950
Like I said,

488
00:28:36,950 --> 00:28:38,290
if you don't have it,
I don't want it either.

489
00:28:39,910 --> 00:28:42,830
Don't think this will make me
feel touched or want to talk to you.

490
00:28:45,910 --> 00:28:46,910
What?

491
00:28:48,250 --> 00:28:49,330
You just admitted it.

492
00:28:51,660 --> 00:28:52,830
Admitted what?

493
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:55,120
You've been ignoring me lately.

494
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,410
What do you mean?

495
00:28:57,410 --> 00:28:58,660
I haven't...

496
00:28:59,290 --> 00:29:01,910
Xi texted me that we eat
before tutoring.

497
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:07,250
Mr. Lin will be there too.

498
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:11,660
Not going?

499
00:29:12,370 --> 00:29:13,410
I'll text him back and say

500
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:14,500
you're still ignoring me.

501
00:29:14,500 --> 00:29:15,620
No. That's not what I meant.

502
00:29:16,950 --> 00:29:19,290
I see. That's what was going on.

503
00:29:20,540 --> 00:29:22,330
Cheers to both of you

504
00:29:23,950 --> 00:29:27,120
for giving up your model student titles.

505
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,000
Cool!

506
00:29:28,010 --> 00:29:31,200
Teaching kids the wrong things.
Shame on us teachers.

507
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:33,160
- Cheers.
- Cheers!

508
00:29:39,700 --> 00:29:41,040
It's boiling. Dig in.

509
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:41,950
Okay.

510
00:29:54,540 --> 00:29:55,750
I have a question.

511
00:29:56,290 --> 00:29:58,370
How did you two meet?

512
00:29:59,660 --> 00:30:00,580
Through a fight.

513
00:30:02,620 --> 00:30:04,290
When we were in college,

514
00:30:04,290 --> 00:30:06,330
he was being bullied and I saved him.

515
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:10,200
After that, we became
unexpectedly close.

516
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,910
We met again abroad

517
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:13,700
and returned not long ago.

518
00:30:13,700 --> 00:30:15,540
Then we found this place for rent,

519
00:30:15,540 --> 00:30:17,950
we decided to lease it

520
00:30:18,290 --> 00:30:19,660
and open a café

521
00:30:20,080 --> 00:30:22,580
to reminisce about our youth.

522
00:30:25,410 --> 00:30:28,330
What does the café's name mean?

523
00:30:28,330 --> 00:30:30,850
(Alors Cafe)

524
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:33,120
Look it up yourself.

525
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:35,040
Aren't you two top students?

526
00:30:41,250 --> 00:30:42,750
Oh? I can't find it.

527
00:30:43,330 --> 00:30:44,790
Isn't it English?

528
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:48,660
But seriously,

529
00:30:49,250 --> 00:30:50,540
you really surprised me

530
00:30:50,950 --> 00:30:52,450
with your impulsiveness.

531
00:30:53,540 --> 00:30:54,660
Do you

532
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:57,830
think it was foolish?

533
00:30:58,910 --> 00:30:59,830
No.

534
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:01,950
Everyone was young once.

535
00:31:03,410 --> 00:31:04,410
Do you ever notice

536
00:31:04,410 --> 00:31:06,750
how people often tell you,

537
00:31:06,750 --> 00:31:07,910
"You'll regret this later"?

538
00:31:09,660 --> 00:31:10,870
So, do you regret it?

539
00:31:13,910 --> 00:31:14,910
Do we look like we do?

540
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:20,620
I just know there's a time
for everything.

541
00:31:20,620 --> 00:31:22,580
If you don't go a little wild
when you're young,

542
00:31:22,580 --> 00:31:24,200
you'll regret it when you're older.

543
00:31:25,330 --> 00:31:26,200
Why?

544
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:29,620
Do you want to live your life

545
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:32,620
always following a set plan?

546
00:31:33,950 --> 00:31:36,700
I think that can wait.

547
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:40,080
While you're young, burn bright

548
00:31:40,450 --> 00:31:42,580
and live with no regrets.

549
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,160
Hey.

550
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:48,790
Do you remember the story
our Mandarin teacher told us?

551
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:51,950
It was about a boy who made a schedule

552
00:31:52,330 --> 00:31:54,290
every summer vacation,

553
00:31:54,290 --> 00:31:55,870
year after year,

554
00:31:56,330 --> 00:31:57,830
from childhood to adulthood.

555
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:01,000
But why did he end up crying?

556
00:32:02,620 --> 00:32:03,750
Yeah, why?

557
00:32:04,910 --> 00:32:06,910
Because he wrote his whole life

558
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:09,790
into his schedules,

559
00:32:10,250 --> 00:32:11,750
into those plans.

560
00:32:12,370 --> 00:32:14,080
But real life

561
00:32:16,620 --> 00:32:17,830
isn't just words on paper.

562
00:32:20,620 --> 00:32:22,290
What are you mumbling about?

563
00:32:24,870 --> 00:32:26,370
